---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Chrome Extension" description="LeadEcho Chrome extension — passive signal collection and reply posting with human-mimicry typing.">
  <h1>Chrome Extension</h1>

  <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
    The LeadEcho Chrome extension (MV3, built with WXT 0.19) runs passively in the background,
    collecting social signals from platforms you browse and posting approved replies
    with human-mimicry timing.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>

  <h3>From Source (Development)</h3>

  <pre><code>cd extension
pnpm install
pnpm build

# In Chrome: go to chrome://extensions
# Enable "Developer mode" (top right toggle)
# Click "Load unpacked" → select the dist/ directory</code></pre>

  <h3>From Chrome Web Store</h3>

  <p>
    Search for "LeadEcho" in the Chrome Web Store, or install directly from the product dashboard
    at <strong>Settings → Chrome Extension → Install</strong>.
  </p>

  <h2>Initial Configuration</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Click the LeadEcho extension icon in your toolbar to open the side panel.</li>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Settings</strong> tab.</li>
    <li>Enter your <strong>API URL</strong> (e.g. <code>https://api.yourdomain.com</code> or <code>http://localhost:8090</code>).</li>
    <li>Paste your <strong>Extension Key</strong> (see below).</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> — the extension will verify the connection.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Getting Your Extension Key</h3>

  <p>In the dashboard, go to <strong>Settings → Extension Token → Generate</strong>.</p>

  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/settings/extension-token
Authorization: Bearer &lt;jwt&gt;

# Response:
&#123;
  "token": "ext_01hx...",
  "created_at": "2025-03-01T10:00:00Z"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <blockquote>
    <p>Extension tokens are long-lived and workspace-scoped. Regenerating invalidates the previous token.</p>
  </blockquote>

  <h2>Passive Signal Collection</h2>

  <p>
    Content scripts run on supported domains and scan the DOM for posts, comments, and threads.
    Signals are de-duplicated locally, buffered, and flushed to the backend periodically.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Platform</th>
        <th>Domain</th>
        <th>Collected Content</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Reddit</td>
        <td><code>reddit.com</code></td>
        <td>Post titles, comment text, author</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Twitter / X</td>
        <td><code>x.com</code></td>
        <td>Tweet text, author handle</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>LinkedIn</td>
        <td><code>linkedin.com</code></td>
        <td>Post text, author name</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Hacker News</td>
        <td><code>news.ycombinator.com</code></td>
        <td>Story titles, comment text</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Flush Behavior</h3>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Trigger</th>
        <th>Condition</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Time-based</td>
        <td>Every 30 seconds</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Buffer-based</td>
        <td>When buffer reaches 20 signals</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3>Signal Ingestion Endpoint</h3>

  <pre><code>POST /api/v1/extension/signals
X-Extension-Key: ext_01hx...
Content-Type: application/json

&#123;
  "signals": [
    &#123;
      "platform": "reddit",
      "content": "We're drowning in client management...",
      "author": "devfounder",
      "url": "https://reddit.com/r/...",
      "collected_at": "2025-03-01T10:00:00Z"
    &#125;
  ]
&#125;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Signals immediately enter the AI scoring pipeline — Stage 1 (rules filter) runs synchronously
    before the response is returned. Stages 2–4 run asynchronously.
  </p>

  <h2>Side Panel</h2>

  <p>The extension side panel has three tabs:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Tab</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Leads</strong></td>
        <td>Recent high-signal mentions (relevance ≥ 7.0) from your workspace</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Queue</strong></td>
        <td>Approved replies pending posting — click "Post" to trigger</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Settings</strong></td>
        <td>API URL and Extension Key configuration</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Reply Posting Flow</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Open the side panel → <strong>Queue</strong> tab.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Post</strong> next to an approved reply.</li>
    <li>The extension opens the target URL in a new tab (or focuses it if already open).</li>
    <li>It locates the reply/comment input field via DOM selectors.</li>
    <li>Types the reply using the human-mimicry engine (see <a href="/docs/reply-posting">Reply Posting</a>).</li>
    <li>Submits the form.</li>
    <li>Marks the reply as posted via <code>PATCH /extension/replies/&#123;id&#125;/mark-posted</code>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Development Build</h2>

  <pre><code>cd extension

# Type checking
pnpm typecheck

# Dev mode with hot reload
pnpm dev

# Production build
pnpm build

# Build output
ls dist/</code></pre>

  <h3>Extension Configuration File</h3>

  <pre><code>// extension/wxt.config.ts
export default defineConfig(&#123;
  manifest: &#123;
    name: 'LeadEcho',
    permissions: ['storage', 'sidePanel', 'activeTab', 'scripting'],
    host_permissions: ['*://reddit.com/*', '*://x.com/*', '*://linkedin.com/*', '*://news.ycombinator.com/*']
  &#125;
&#125;);</code></pre>

  <h2>Permissions Explained</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Permission</th>
        <th>Why It's Needed</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>storage</code></td>
        <td>Persist API URL and extension key locally</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>sidePanel</code></td>
        <td>Show the side panel UI</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>activeTab</code></td>
        <td>Access the currently active tab for posting</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>scripting</code></td>
        <td>Inject content scripts for DOM interaction</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>host_permissions</td>
        <td>Read and interact with supported platform pages</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocsLayout>
